review_blob: Bomber after a bike ride to a lake. Semi-sweet aroma with notes of fig and dates. Full-bodied, sweet, dark fruit flavor. Long, smooth, malty sweet finish.
beer_name: No-Li Expo Series Big Bang Barley Wine

review_blob: Batch 7, super foamy. Light, honey, golden color. Dry and tart aroma. Dry, and a bit funky. Bit of spice and herbal notes. Subtle sweetness in finish.
Bomber. Light amber copper in color. Rich, earthy taste. Good, balanced smoked chile flavors. Subtle and lingering slow burn. Tastes like a sun-drenched dirt field, in a good way.

Bottle. Light amber and hazy. Soft white head, not much retention. Strong malt flavor, contains some dark fruit sweetness. Sweetness focused in the middle, strong caramel flavor. Bitter, but not overpowering, finish.
